This paper deals with the analysis and optimization of neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments are conducted on image datasets, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses vulnerability and adversarial attacks, which are relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CR). The use of active subspace as a model reduction method is related to optimization and efficiency, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or neural networks (cs.NE).
